<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="395" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.415/16</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Brazilian Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Alencar</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-13"><hi rend="italic">February 13,
                                    1922</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have received
                            instructions from the President of Brazil to invite the Government of
                            the United States <pb facs="0778" n="658" xml:id="pg_658"/> to attend
                            the Centennial Celebration of the Independence of Brazil, in September
                            next at Rio de Janeiro.</p>
                        <p>I am transmitting to you this invitation by letter, not being able to
                            call on you before your departure tomorrow, confined, as I am, by
                            direction of my physician, to my bed since several days ago, and I do
                            not know for how much longer.</p>
                        <p>With the expressions [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">A. de Alencar</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>